AIM:
To develop a basic Spring MVC application using annotation-based configuration only, without using web.xml or any Spring XML files. The application should include a controller to accept user requests and display employee details through the MVC architecture using Spring Boot and Thymeleaf templates.

PROCEDURE:
Create a Spring Boot project with the required dependencies:
Spring Web
Thymeleaf
Create the package structure (Edu.Task_9) and add required classes:
Task9Application.java (main class)
Employee.java (model)
EmployeeRepository.java (in-memory storage)
EmployeeController.java (Spring MVC controller)
Define the Employee model class
Include fields such as id, name, and department.
Provide constructors, getters, setters, and a toString() method.
Create the EmployeeRepository
Store employee records in memory using a list or map.
Provide methods like findAll() and findById().
Develop the EmployeeController class
Annotate with @Controller.
Map URLs using @GetMapping or @RequestMapping.
Use Model to pass employee data to the view.
Return Thymeleaf views such as home and employee.
Create Thymeleaf Templates under src/main/resources/templates:
home.html → entry page with a link to view employees
employee.html → displays employee details dynamically
Run the project using the Spring Boot main class (Task9Application).
Open browser → visit:
http://localhost:8080/employees
Verify MVC Flow
Controller receives request
Repository provides data
Controller sends data to view
Thymeleaf renders the final HTML page

