RESULT:
Thus, a basic Spring MVC application was successfully developed using annotation-based configuration only, without any XML files. A controller was created to handle user requests, fetch data from the repository, and pass employee details to the Thymeleaf view.
The application demonstrated the complete Spring MVC flow—Model, View, and Controller—using Spring Boot, annotations, and in-memory data storage.
